    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Readme\nThis chatbot loads any file attached into a vector database with the **Load Data Flow**, before handling the user/human query (**Chatbot w/ Context and Retrieval flow**)\n\nThis allows to load several large documents and keep access to the content of each of them, when required, based on the human's queries and the context of the conversation.\n\nYou can modify the behavior by modifying the following parameters:\n- AI Agent Node:\n    - system message\n- Chatbot Model:\n    - model selection\n    - Temperature\n    -  Context length \n- Simple Memory:\n    - number of conversation elements kept\n\n### Usage\n- Publish the workflow and open the conversation window\n- Upload one or several files and ask question\n\n### More info:\n- Key node for this workflow is the `Simple Vector Store` node, used in several configurations:\n    - \"add document to vector store\"\n    - \"retrieve document (as tool to agent)\"\n- Check `Simple Vector Store` [node documentation](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/cluster-nodes/root-nodes/n8n-nodes-langchain.vectorstoreinmemory)\n- Check `Default Data Loader` [node documentation](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/cluster-nodes/sub-nodes/n8n-nodes-langchain.documentdefaultdataloader/)\n- Check [docs on RAG in n8n](https://docs.n8n.io/advanced-ai/rag-in-n8n/).\n",
        "height": 796,
        "width": 440,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -752,
        -656
